hen Freiheit. Die Beiträge des Bandes zeigen: Wenn beide Fragen die gleichen Antworten kommen, kann die Lust am Gestalten losgehen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCommunication in design. 0aDesignxPhilosophy. 0aDesignxSocial aspects. 4aDIY. 4aDemokratie. 4aFreiheit. 4aGesellschaft. 4aGestaltung. 4aKonsumkritik. 4aKritik. 4aMedien. 4aPartizipation. 4aPolitik. 4aStadtplanung. 4aWahrnehmung. 4aÄsthetik. 7aDESIGN / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aConsumer Critique.  aCritique.  aDemocracy.  aDiy.  aLiberty.  aMedia.  aParticipation.  aPerception.  aPolitics.  aShaping.  aSociety.  aUrban Planning.1 aAchatz, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArnold, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbert, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOffermanns, Ingo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeiter, Anne D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPohler, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRecklies, Mara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodatz, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodatz, Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchweppenhäuser, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmolarski, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc